Key Match Events: Scottie Barnes had 33 points and 13 rebounds.
Immanuel Quickley contributed 21 points and a season-high 15 assists.
Gradey Dick scored 22 points and Ochai Agbaji added 14.
Cam Johnson scored 24 points and D’Angelo Russell had 22 in his return to Brooklyn.
Keon Johnson scored 17 points and Nic Claxton had 16 points and 10 rebounds.
Noah Clowney (lower back) did not return after a hard fall late in the third quarter.
Maxwell Lewis had to be helped off after appearing to injure his left knee late in the fourth.
Quickley assisted on four straight baskets, including 3-pointers by Dick and Agbaji, as Toronto stretched a seven-point lead to 15, 114-99, with just over five minutes remaining.
Brooklyn’s Ben Simmons scored just two points.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Toronto Raptors snapped an 11-game losing streak by beating the Brooklyn Nets 130-113.
The Raptors were coming off a franchise-worst 54-point loss at Boston on New Year’s Eve.
Toronto scored 71 points against the Celtics, the fewest by any NBA team this season.
D’Angelo Russell was acquired from the Lakers on Dec. 29, rejoining the team he played from 2017 to 2019.
